    "en": {
      "question": "In a redox reaction, the substance that gains electrons is said to be:",
      "options": [
        "Oxidized",
        "Reduced",
        "Decomposed",
        "Displaced"
      ],
      "explanation": "Reduction is gain of electrons. Oxidation is loss of electrons. In a redox reaction, one substance is oxidized (loses e-) and another is reduced (gains e-)."
